## Deployment

We deploy via the platform named in the *Deployment Guide*. Every deployment is triggered by a tag on `main`; we do not deploy from a feature branch.

Rollbacks are a one-command operation; the command and the rollback triggers are recorded in the *Deployment Guide*. The on-call engineer is responsible for executing them when the *Incident Response Plan* triggers.

## Observability

Every service emits structured logs, metrics and traces. Logs are JSON, indexed by request id, and retained for the period recorded in the *Data Retention Policy*. Metrics are exposed in Prometheus format and scraped by the platform's managed monitoring.

The on-call dashboard is the single source of truth during an incident. The dashboard's URL and login owner are recorded in the *Domain and Account Register*.

## Runbook

The day-to-day operational runbook lives alongside this document at `04-engineering/16-oncall-runbook.md`. It covers the alerts that page humans, the steps to triage each, and the escalation path when a triage step fails.

If a runbook step is wrong, fix the runbook in the same pull request that fixes the underlying cause. Stale runbooks cost trust the next time an incident lands.

